By Onyebuchi Ezigbo in Abuja The National Working Committee (NWC) of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has again rescheduled governorship primaries in Lagos, Enugu and Adamawa states. The party also changed the mode of primaries for Enugu and Adamawa states from indirect to direct primaries. In a statement issued by the acting National Publicity Secretary Yekini Nabene, the party said the new date for Lagos Governorship Primaries is now Tuesday, October 2, while Enugu and Adamawa direct governorship primaries is to come up on Thursday, October 4.